56.5	Thomas_Nagel	Thomas Nagel	Thomas Nagel (born July 4, 1937 in Belgrade, in present-day Serbia) is an American philosopher, currently University Professor of Philosophy and Law at New York University, where he has taught since 1980. His main areas of philosophical interest are philosophy of mind, political philosophy and ethics. He is well known for his critique of reductionist accounts of the mind in his essay "What Is It Like to Be a Bat?" (1974), and for his contributions to deontological and liberal moral and political theory in The Possibility of Altruism (1970) and subsequent writings.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/1/10/Thomas_Nagel_teaching_Ethics.JPG/250px-Thomas_Nagel_teaching_Ethics.JPG
